#: ../../source/guides/harvesting/activating-delegated-harvesting.rst:48
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/harvesting/activating-delegated-harvesting.rst:50
msgid ""
":ref:`Delegated harvesting <delegated-harvesting>` enables accounts to "
"receive rewards from creating new blocks without running a node. At the "
"same time, it allows nodes to benefit from an account's (possibly higher)"
" :ref:`importance score <importance-calculation>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/harvesting/activating-delegated-harvesting.rst:52
msgid ""
"The account's **private key** is never shared with the node so this "
"method is inherently safer than :ref:`local harvesting <local-"
"harvesting>` since all nodes must be publicly accessible and therefore "
"open to attack. For this reason it is recommended that node owners also "
"use delegated harvesting even though setting up a node for local "
"harvesting is simpler."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/harvesting/activating-delegated-harvesting.rst:54
msgid "Summary of the required steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/harvesting/activating-delegated-harvesting.rst:56
msgid ""
"Delegate the **main account (M)** importance to a **remote account (R)** "
"using an :ref:`AccountKeyLinkTransaction <account-key-link-transaction>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/harvesting/activating-delegated-harvesting.rst:58
msgid ""
"Link the main account **M** to a **VRF account (V)** for randomized block"
" production and account selection using a :ref:`VrfKeyLinkTransaction "
"<vrf-key-link-transaction>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/harvesting/activating-delegated-harvesting.rst:60
msgid ""
"Link the main account **M** to a node in order to harvest through that "
"node using a :ref:`NodeKeyLinkTransaction <node-key-link-transaction>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/harvesting/activating-delegated-harvesting.rst:62
msgid ""
"Request the node to add the remote account **R** as a delegated harvester"
" using a :ref:`PersistentDelegationRequestTransaction <persistent-"
"delegation-request-transaction>`. Conversely, if the node configuration "
"is accessible, the remote account's private key can be set in the node "
"configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/harvesting/activating-delegated-harvesting.rst:64
msgid ""
"Please note that it is entirely up to the node to comply with the "
"request. Some nodes can be asked for their current list of delegated "
"harvesters but this information is not always available (see :ref"
":`delegated-harvesting-verifying-activation` below)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/harvesting/activating-delegated-harvesting.rst:68
msgid "Prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/harvesting/activating-delegated-harvesting.rst:70
msgid ""
"Complete the :doc:`sending mosaics and messages between two accounts "
"<../transfer/sending-a-transfer-transaction>` guide to have a basic "
"understanding of transactions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/harvesting/activating-delegated-harvesting.rst:72
msgid ""
"Before you can activate delegated harvesting, you need the following "
"items:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/harvesting/activating-delegated-harvesting.rst:74
msgid ""
"A **Main account (M)** with at least **10,000** |networkcurrency| to be "
":ref:`eligible <account_eligibility>` and then some more to pay for "
"transaction fees. This is the account that will receive the harvesting "
"fees. Keep its secret key secret at all times."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/harvesting/activating-delegated-harvesting.rst:76
msgid ""
"A **Remote account (R)** that will act as a proxy between **M** and the "
"node. This account **must have never sent or received any transaction**, "
"and it cannot be involved in any transaction while it is a delegated "
"account."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/harvesting/activating-delegated-harvesting.rst:78
msgid ""
"A **VRF account (V)** that has never sent or received any transactions. "
"It is a regular account used to add randomness to the account selection "
"process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/harvesting/activating-delegated-harvesting.rst:80
msgid ""
"The **node's public TLS key**. This is the key the node uses to "
"authenticate data for transport over TLS and is typically provided by the"
" node owner."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/harvesting/activating-delegated-harvesting.rst:82
msgid "Optionally:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/harvesting/activating-delegated-harvesting.rst:84
msgid ""
"An **Announcer account (A)** with enough |networkcurrency| to pay for "
"transaction fees. By announcing the final harvesting delegation request "
"through this account instead of **M**, even the fact that **M** is "
"involved in delegated harvesting is hidden from the network. Use this "
"account for added privacy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/harvesting/activating-delegated-harvesting.rst:86
msgid ""
"Refer to the :doc:`Creating an account <../account/creating-an-account>` "
"guide to know how to create new accounts if you need to."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/harvesting/activating-delegated-harvesting.rst:88
msgid ""
"The bash code snippets make use of :doc:`symbol-cli <../../cli>` and "
"assume that the **main account (M)** is set as the **default** profile. "
